'''Shimanagashi''' ({{Lang-ja|島流し}}) is a form of punishment where people are banished to small islands.{{citation needed|date=May 2013}} It was created during the [[feudalism|feudal period]] in [[Japan]], where political offenders were often sent away and confined on the island of Sado in the Sea of Japan<ref>{{Cite journal|date=2017-12-12|title=Sado, Niigata|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Sado,_Niigata&oldid=815022965|journal=Wikipedia|language=en}}</ref>.

